HEADWORD: Outcry
<hw>Out"cry`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
vehement or loud cry; a cry of distress, alarm, opposition, or
detestation; clamor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Sale at public auction.</def>
<rj><au>Massinger.</au> <au>Thackeray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outdare</ent>⟦br⟧
